download java
configure environment variables
launch eclipse IDE
create a new java project
download webdriver jar
Download selenium server (Grid) or selenium client and webdriver language (java) bindings
Create c:/browserdriver folder
download the browser driver you want to use and put them in the c:/browserdriver folder you created
set property for webdriver: System.setProperty("webdriver.chrome.driver", "c:\\browserdriver\\chromedriver.exe"); might not be neccessary

SETUP SELENIUM DEVELOPMENT ENVIRONMENT
download selenium server and add it to the project library build path as an external jar file
